# WatchAgent – Polling & Logging Rule Contract

These rules define mandatory behavior for all polling, event detection, logging, and pipeline code in this project. Cursor MUST follow these rules when generating or modifying code.

---

# 1. POLLING ARCHITECTURE (STRICT)

## 1.1 Role Separation
- polling_service.py MUST ONLY handle orchestration
- It MUST NOT contain:
  - event detection logic
  - statistical logic
  - ORM model definitions
  - data transformation logic

---

## 1.2 Required Polling Loop Structure

ALL polling implementations MUST follow this pattern:

```python
for city in cities:
    db = SessionLocal()
    try:
        weather = fetch_weather(city)

        if is_duplicate(db, city, weather):
            log_info("[DUPLICATE_SKIPPED] city=" + city)
            continue

        reading = save_reading(db, weather)
        events = detect_events(db, city, weather)

        if events:
            save_events(db, city, events)

    except Exception as e:
        log_error("[POLL_FAILURE] city=" + city + " error=" + str(e))

    finally:
        db.close()
```

Rules:
- NEVER change execution order
- ALWAYS deduplicate before saving
- NEVER allow exceptions to escape city loop
- ALWAYS isolate each city in try/except

---

# 2. FAILURE HANDLING (STRICT)

- Failure in one city MUST NOT stop polling other cities
- ALL exceptions inside city loop MUST be caught

Required log format:

```
[POLL_FAILURE] city=<city> error=<message>
```

Rules:
- NEVER crash polling loop
- NEVER silently ignore exceptions
- NEVER rethrow exceptions from city loop

---

# 3. RETRY RULES

- Retry logic MUST be bounded
- MUST use asyncio.sleep (never blocking sleep)
- Retry count MUST come from configuration

Retry log format:

```
[FETCH_RETRY] city=<city> attempt=<n>
```

After retry failure:
- MUST log warning
- MUST NOT crash system

---

# 4. LOGGING CONTRACT (STRICT)

ALL logs MUST follow:

```
[EVENT_TYPE] key=value key=value
```

Allowed EVENT_TYPE values:
- POLL_FAILURE
- READING_SAVED
- EVENT_CREATED
- DUPLICATE_SKIPPED
- FETCH_RETRY
- NO_EVENTS

Log rules:
- INFO for success
- WARNING for recoverable issues
- ERROR for unexpected failures
- NO multiline logs
- NO unstructured prints

---

# 5. PROCESSING PIPELINE ORDER (MANDATORY)

Every city cycle MUST follow:

1. fetch weather
2. deduplicate
3. save reading
4. detect events
5. save events

Rules:
- Order MUST NEVER change
- Duplicate readings MUST NOT trigger event detection
- Event detection MUST only run after saving reading

---

# 6. DEDUPLICATION RULES

- MUST run before saving reading
- MUST compare only latest city reading
- MUST skip duplicates

Log format:
```
[DUPLICATE_SKIPPED] city=<city>
```

---

# 7. DATABASE RULES

- Session MUST be created per city
- Session MUST be closed in finally block
- Commit ONLY after successful creation
- MUST rollback on DB error
- DB failures MUST NOT crash polling loop

---

# 8. EVENT ENGINE RULES

- Event detection MUST NOT break polling flow
- Failure in event detection MUST NOT stop pipeline

Event format:
```
(event_type: str, description: str)
```

---

# 9. ASYNC RULES

- MUST use async/await everywhere possible
- MUST use asyncio.sleep (NOT time.sleep)
- MUST NOT block polling loop
- MUST NOT run uncontrolled parallel tasks

---

# 10. CONFIGURATION RULES

NEVER hardcode:
- cities
- polling interval
- retry limits
- API timeout
- endpoints

ALL must come from settings.

---

# 11. STABILITY RULES

System MUST be resilient to:
- API failure
- malformed responses
- DB errors
- timeout errors
- event failures

System MUST:
- continue polling indefinitely
- recover automatically on next cycle
- never crash due to single-city failure